<TITLE> Boy, 10, killed in Chapainawabganj blast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, Mar 4 (bdnews24.com)A policeman's 10 year-old son was killed, and two other children were injured in suspected grenade blast at Chapainawabganj Sadar Police Station Wednesday. "The children were playing on the police station premises near a rubbish dump which suddenly exploded. It happened around 12.30pm," said OC Amirul Islam. "Al Amin, son of ASI Ataur Rahman, was critically injured and died at Rajshahi Medical College Hospital," said islam. Seven-year-old Mamunur Rashid, son of ASI Rafiqul Islam, and 10-year-old Mehedi Hasan, son of a rickshaw-puller, were also injured, said the OC. He said they suspected a grenade was planted among the rubbish. bdne
